<p>1924. Two married couples find themselves quarantined on a small island in the South Pacific during a torrential storm. Enter Sadie Thompson, a woman with a dark past and a bottle of good whiskey. Secrets are revealed and sexual tensions ignite and explode in this new musical adaptation of the classic Somerset Maugham story. From five-time Tony-nominated composer and lyricist Michael John LaChiusa (<em>Giant, The Wild Party, Marie Christine</em>), Tony-nominated writer Sybille Pearson (<em>Baby, Giant</em>) and director Barry Edelstein (Nathan Englander&#8217;s <em>The Twenty- Seventh Man</em>, Steve Martin&#8217;s <em>The Underpants</em>).</p>
            
